    ## All dependencies are approved.

    Dependency characteristics

    • countVertices: The amount of recursive dependencies DrugExposureDiagnostics depends on.
    • countEdges: The total amount of imports of all dependencies.
    • meanDegree: The average amount of imports per dependency.
    • meanDistance: The average dependency layers between DrugExposureDiagnostics and all other recursive dependencies.

    Cyclomatic Complexity

    Cyclomatic Complexity is a software metric used to indicate the complexity of a program. It is a quantitative measure of the number of linearly independent paths through a programâ€™s source code. It was developed by Thomas J. McCabe, Sr.Â in 1976.

    And is calculated as follows: \(M = E - N + 2P\)

    The complexity score is interpreted as follows:

    • 1-10 Simple procedure, little risk
    • 11-20 More complex, moderate risk
    • 21-50 Complex, high risk
    • >50 Untestable code, very high risk
